{
  "text": "Grasslands are imperiled ecosystems worldwide [CITATION_1] . For example, globally since 1700, the conversion rate of natural grasslands to farmlands (50%) has been twice that of forests [CITATION_2] , and temperate grasslands are among the world's most poorly protected biomes [CITATION_3] . Many grasslands have been maintained by human intervention and show abrupt declines. For example, in the past century, semi-natural grasslands (maintained by human intervention without a significant application of chemicals and sowing) in southeastern Sweden decreased by 96% via afforestation [CITATION_4] . The origin and history of grasslands are therefore important for their contemporary management [CITATION_5] .",
